60|$|All {{that day}} Mowgli {{sat in the}} cave tending his <b>fire</b> <b>pot</b> and dipping dry {{branches}} into it {{to see how they}} looked. He found a branch that satisfied him, and in the evening when Tabaqui came to the cave and told him rudely enough that he was wanted at the Council Rock, he laughed till Tabaqui ran away. Then Mowgli went to the Council, still laughing.|$|E
