50|$|Given the {{time-consuming}} {{nature of}} early firestarting, humans eventually {{began to use}} earthenware vessels, or <b>fire</b> <b>pots,</b> in which slow-burning fires could by kept alight indefinitely by using small quantities of fuel. Nomadic people could carry these small fires with them, using them to start larger fires for their evening camps.|$|R
